@Bruce, in case anyone sees this reply:

I have had Global Entry for many years. I had the same driver’s license number for decades (and RealID for years). In 2024, Florida passed legislation to change driver’s license numbers because they embedded personal information. So when my license expired last year, I was issued a new number. 

It never occurred to me to update my info with Global Entry, and also my voter’s registration (which is tied to one’s driver’s license in many states). A friend mentioned it, and I updated both yesterday. Two important things to remember to update if you have received a new driver’s license number!

