I'm with you both on the night sky's beauty, what little I manage to see of it through the urban light spill. (I note that you both seem to be non-metropolitans.)
But anyone who's a parent or grandparent of a child between six and 12-ish, here's your reminder to get them a pocket guide to the night skies and book next Saturday night for an hour of going outside and staring up and out. I was a science girl and had the advantage of the prairies' night skies and a culturally encouraged fascination with the moon's phases. But even in the big city with the small sky, attention can be paid to a larger universe,  beautiful despite or perhaps because of being beyond our reach.

